The article discusses the Agriculture and Food Security Expo co-hosted by the U.S. Agency for International Development (USAID), U.S. Department of Agriculture (USDA), and Confederation of Indian Industries (CII) in India. The expo showcases innovative tools and technologies developed by U.S. and Indian institutions to revolutionize the lives of Indian farmers. Some of the exhibitors include the Central Institute of Agricultural Engineering (CIAE), IFFCO Kisan Sanchar Limited (IKSL), Pioneer Hi-Bred International, Mahindra & Mahindra, PepsiCo, Aries Agro, Digital Green (DG), ITC, Jain Irrigation Systems, and Ingersoll Rand. These companies have developed various tools and technologies such as compact farming tools for female farmers, mobile services for farmers, hybrid seeds, small tractors, agricultural videos, internet kiosks, irrigation systems, and refrigerated vans. The expo aims to highlight the potential of partnership between India and the United States in addressing global challenges related to agriculture and food security.